title.narrative: Investing for impact against Tuberculosis- Scaling up Private Sector participation in TB Control

description.narrative: Nigeria - Tuberculosis - Institute of Human Virology Nigeria - IHVN. This program has the following goals: To ensure universal access to high-quality, patient-centred, prevention, diagnosis and treatment services for TB, TB/HIV and DR-TB by 2020.. Responsive and resilient health systems that promote universal access to quality health care services by 2020. The objectives of this program are: To increase case notification rate of all forms of TB from 55.1/100,000 population in 2017 to 287 per 100,000 population in 2020. To increase TB treatment success rate from 85% in 2017 to 90% in 2020 among drug susceptible patients. To enrol 100% of diagnosed DR-TB patients on appropriate treatment by 2020. Strengthen health systems for delivery of packages of essential health care services

title.narrative: Number of TB cases with RR-TB and/or MDR-TB notified
Number of notified TB cases (all forms) contributed by non-national TB program providers – private/non-governmental facilities
Percentage of TB patients with DST result for at least Rifampicin among the total number of notified (new and retreatment) cases in the same year
MDR TB-other 2: Percentage of presumptive DR-TB cases that received tesing for DR-TB (RR-TB and/or MDR-TB)
Number of cases with RR-TB and/or MDR-TB that began second-line treatment
Percentage of DST laboratories showing adequate performance on External Quality Assurance
Percentage of previously treated TB patients receiving DST (bacteriologically positive cases only)
MDR TB-other 1: Number of cases with drug resistant TB (RR-TB and/or MDR-TB) that began second-line treatment

Treatment success rate- all forms: Percentage of TB cases, all forms, bacteriologically confirmed plus clinically diagnosed, successfully treated (cured plus treatment completed) among all TB cases registered for treatment during a specified period, new and relapse cases
